manufacturerProductDescription.media_text: AMD Ryzen Threadripper 2920X Advanced Successor to the World's First 16-core Desktop Processor* The Power to Game, Stream, and Create Simultaneously. For serious Enthusiasts, Prosumers and Creators, AMD designed the new 2nd Gen Ryzen Threadripper 2920X. When you need to game, stream, and produce content at the same time, this is the new processor of choice. Boasting 16 high-performance cores capable of harnessing 32 parallel threads, the Ryzen Threadripper 2950X delivers the computing power you need to dispatch your heaviest workloads, simultaneously, with extreme prejudice.

Amp-Up Your Designs Stage dive into intricate 3D modeling projects and harness full suites of creative software to apply bewitching additions, adjustments and animations. Tame the Most Taxing Programs For every stage of your creative process, including VFX modeling, editing, tracking and mastering; enough power for most resource intensive programs. Render Scenes in Living Detail The 2nd Gen Ryzen Threadripper processor is capable of endowing your art with the authentic atmospheres that bring digital worlds to life. Game for Work or Game for Play Experience game levels as you develop them, test new content in real-time, or just game for the fun of it while your PC compiles and renders.
2nd Gen AMD Ryzen Threadripper: The Biggest, Heaviest, Fastest Desktop Processor

2nd Gen AMD Ryzen Threadripper Create with Heavy Metal Unleash the brute force of up to 32-cores and 64-threads of raw processing power with 2nd Generation AMD Ryzen™ Threadripper™ processors. Unlocked for overclocking; Advanced 'Zen' architecture; AMD SenseMI Technology. Up to 16 cores and 32 threads for lightning-fast creative workloadsAn unprecedented 64 PCIe Gen3 lanes to meet large GPU and NVMe needs40MB of combined cache for rapid access to large data setsQuad channel DDR4 with available ECC support for reliable throughput

The Ultimate Desktop Platform Future-Proof X399 The Ultimate Desktop Platform: AMD’s X399 chipset supports both 1st and 2nd Gen AMD Ryzen Threadripper processors (BIOS update may be required). Built for creators who game, and gamers who create, the scalable AMD X399 chipset offers unprecedented expansion for serious multi-GPU and NVMe arrays. Meanwhile: quad channel DDR4, available ECC support, and unlocked overclocking make X399 a lock for users that depend on serious computing. Now featuring AMD StoreMI storage acceleration technology.

FOX VFX Labs on AMD Ryzen Threadripper A Game Changer in Filmmaking Fox VFX Lab is leading the way in virtual production, enabling storytellers to make real-time on-set aesthetic decisions by experiencing virtual environments at scale. Learn how AMD Ryzen Threadripper Processors deliver the necessary compute capability to power a new era of cinematic pre-visualization backed AMD EPYC processors for final frame rendering. Fox VFX Lab is an industry-leading virtual production and motion capture company behind some of Hollywood’s biggest blockbusters.

reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Functions exactly as expected.
reviews.reviewText: I have had no issues with it, it functions exactly as expected.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on March 19, 2020
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Overkill, just the way I like it.
reviews.reviewText: This thing is a monster CPU. There's no lag no matter what I've thrown at it unless I deliberately ran something to run up all 24 threads and then try gaming on top of that. Even apps that aren't able to multi thread run great, as each core is plenty fast enough. If you download the Ryzen Master program you can see each core in real time; clock speed, temp, etc. I am so glad to see AMD processors making Intel sweat again.One thing to note, you are going to want a liquid cooler setup for this thing, it's a 180W CPU and there's no way you wanna air-cool that.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on April 23, 2019
reviews.reviewText: This thing is an absolute monster at rendering. Stability isn't great. I've had to tweak the heck out of my BIOS settings to make it not constantly crap out on me. Now that I have it stable, I get fantastic performance. Considering that the equivalent Intel CPU is something like twice the price, this is absolutely worth the price. I would recommend using a Gigabyte motherboard and RAM 3000mhz or faster.For clarity, this CPU is not the best for gaming. It requires a lot of tuning and settings tweaking to get it to an optimal framerate. This is not a gaming CPU. Definitely do not get it if you're just going to be gaming on your system.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 24, 2019
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Good workstation CPU
reviews.reviewText: First off, if you are looking at this (or any Threadripper CPU) for gaming, look elsewhere. Threadripper is decent for games, but the Ryzen 9 3900x or pretty much any recent Intel Core i7 or above will give you better performance for less money. That said, if your workload is more compute heavy and multithreaded, like video editing, 3D modeling and rendering, application development, and the like, it's hard to go wrong with Threadripper. The particular CPU I got overclocks well, and I was able to easily hit 4.25 GHz on all cores, though your mileage may vary. The only problem I have with this part is how much heat it puts out.
es un monstruo para una desktop e ideal para el armado en una workstation.
